I have been researching Ethereum's ERC-4337 token standard and am excited to share my primer series.

I delve into the workings of ERC-4337, terminology, advantages, how it compares to other token standards, and how developers and users can benefit from this standard.

Here's the link: bit.ly/erc4337
Pitch your friends. Get their honest humble opinion. Work on it. Repeat.

As far as I correctly understand, ERC-4337 merges the two account types into a new one & users can program different mechanisms to retrieve their private keys.

Instead of deploying a new contract per user, wallets can now function as smart contracts.

More here: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4337
